    {
      "id": "47e56f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL Courses related to East Asian philosophy, religion, and culture are recommended and may be transferable for credit toward major requirements upon consultation with the undergraduate major advisor (UMA). We encourage Students to take Chinese, Japanese, or Tibetan language courses if they are offered at their college. Students will receive transfer credit for language courses taken at their community college. However, all UC Berkeley students must take a placement exam for Chinese or Japanese (there are no placement exams for Tibetan) to ensure enrollment in a course at the correct level for their language skills. Because language courses vary among colleges, a student may need to repeat an introductory or intermediate-level course if necessary. The department undergraduate advisor will work with students to create a program plan to complete their major requirements by their expected graduation date, regardless of which language course is their first. Please note: Advanced Placement (AP) and International Baccalaureate (IB) exams will not satisfy the requirements for this major. Prerequisites Students are required to successfully (grade C or higher) complete one language course at UC Berkeley and one course from List A (see the Berkeley Guide or department website ) before declaring the major. More Information The Berkeley Catalog and the department website provide more information about major requirements and course information. Advising: Students with questions about transferring into the major in East Asian Languages and Cultures are encouraged to contact our undergraduate major advisor: Cassandra Dunn Department Website: http://ealc.berkeley.edu/ Email: cassandrajj@berkeley.edu Appointments: Schedule an appointment (in-person or remotely).",
      "contentHtml": "<p><strong>PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL </strong></p><p><br></p><p>Courses related to East Asian philosophy, religion, and culture are recommended and may be transferable for credit toward major requirements upon consultation with the undergraduate major advisor (UMA).</p><p><br></p><p>We encourage Students to take Chinese, Japanese, or Tibetan language courses if they are offered at their college. Students will receive transfer credit for language courses taken at their community college. However, all UC Berkeley students must take a<a href=\"https://ealc.berkeley.edu/programs/undergraduate/placement-exams\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"> placement exam for Chinese or Japanese</a> (there are no placement exams for Tibetan) to ensure enrollment in a course at the correct level for their language skills. Because language courses vary among colleges, a student may need to repeat an introductory or intermediate-level course if necessary. The department undergraduate advisor will work with students to create a program plan to complete their major requirements by their expected graduation date, regardless of which language course is their first.</p><p><br></p><p>Please note: Advanced Placement (AP) and International Baccalaureate (IB) exams will not satisfy the requirements for this major.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong></p><p>Students are required to successfully (grade C or higher) complete one language course at UC Berkeley and one course from List A (see the <a href=\"https://guide.berkeley.edu/undergraduate/degree-programs/east-asian-religion-thought-culture/#abouttheprogramtext\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Berkeley Guide</a> or <a href=\"https://ealc.berkeley.edu/programs/undergraduate/undergraduate-requirements/east-asian-religion-major-requirements\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">department website</a>) before declaring the major.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>More Information</strong></p><p>The <a href=\"https://undergraduate.catalog.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Berkeley Catalog</a> and the <a href=\"https://ealc.berkeley.edu/programs/undergraduate/undergraduate-requirements/east-asian-religion-major-requirements\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">department website</a> provide more information about major requirements and course information.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Advising:</strong></p><p>Students with questions about transferring into the major in East Asian Languages and Cultures are encouraged to contact our undergraduate major advisor:</p><p>Cassandra Dunn</p><p>Department Website: <a href=\"http://ealc.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://ealc.berkeley.edu/</a></p><p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:cassandrajj@berkeley.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">cassandrajj@berkeley.edu</a></p><p>Appointments: <a href=\"https://calendly.com/cassandra-dunn-ug-advisor\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Schedule an appointment (in-person or remotely).</a></p>"
    }
